Adds the global p-value for a categorical variables in tbl_uvregression objects

add_global.tbl_uvregression.Rd

This function uses Anova from the car package with type = "III" to calculate global p-values. If a needed class of model is not supported by Anova, please put in an issue at https://github.com/ddsjoberg/gtsummary/issues to request support.

# S3 method for tbl_uvregression
add_global(x, ...)

Arguments

x

object with class tbl_uvregression from the tbl_uvregression function
...

arguments to be passed to Anova. Adding test.statistic = can change the type of test (e.g. Likelihood-ratio, Wald, etc.).

Examples

tbl_uvregression(
  trial,
  method = "glm",
  y = "response",
  method.args = list(family = binomial),
  exponentiate = TRUE
) %>%
  add_global()
